Having aided Pittacus to deliver his country from the tyrants which oppressed it, he quarrelled with this friend, when the people of Mitylene had placed uncontrolled power in the hands of the latter3 and some injurious verses which he composed against Pittacus, caused himself and his adherents to be driven into exile.
